This is the ChangeLog of SystemRescueCd (x86 edition)
=====================================================

Homepage:.......http://www.sysresccd.org/
Forums:.........http://www.sysresccd.org/forums/
Manual:.........http://www.sysresccd.org/Online-Manual-EN

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.4.0 (2014-10-13)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.10.55 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.14.20 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated filesystem tools: btrfs-progs-3.16.1 + reiser4progs-1.0.9
* Updated partclone to sys-block/partclone-0.2.73
* Updated perl language package to dev-lang/perl-5.18.2-r1
* Updated to a new major portage version: portage-2.2.8

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.3.1 (2014-09-10)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.10.53 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels: updated to stable linux-3.14.17 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated GNU Parted to 3.2 and GParted to 0.19.1 (Bug fix release)
* Updated file systems: e2fsprogs-1.42.12, btrfs-progs-3.14.2, fuse-exfat-1.1.0

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.3.0 (2014-07-07)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.10.45 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels: updated to stable linux-3.14.9 (altker32 + altker64)
* Dropped TrueCrypt package (Migration recommended by official website)
* Added support for the ruby language (dev-lang/ruby-2.0.0_p353)
* Updated btrfs utilities to sys-fs/btrfs-progs-3.14.1
* Updated GParted to 0.19.0 (Bug fix release)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.2.0 (2014-04-15)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.10.35 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels: updated to stable linux-3.13.10 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated XOrg graphical environment and drivers to xorg-server-1.15.0
* Updated LVM (Logical Volume Manager) to version 2.02.103 in the initramfs
* Dropped ClamAV to save 74MB in the ISO image

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.1.0 (2014-03-11)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.10.32 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels: updated to stable linux-3.13.5 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated NBD client in initramfs to sys-block/nbd-3.2 (Network Block Device)
* Updated ntfs filesystem in userspace driver to sys-fs/ntfs3g-2014.2.15
* Updated squashfs-tools to sys-fs/squashfs-tools-4.2_p20140119
* Updated perl language package to dev-lang/perl-5.16.3
* Updated sys-auth packages (polkit, pambase, consolekit)
* Updated fsarchiver to 0.6.19 (bugfix release)
* Updated OpenRC to sys-apps/openrc-0.12.4

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.0.1 (2014-02-24)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.10.30 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels: stable linux-3.12.12 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated Offline Windows Password & Registry Editor floopy image to 2014-02-01
* Added app-arch/lz4 (Fast Compression) + app-arch/lrzip-0.44 (Long Range ZIP)
* Updated fsarchiver to 0.6.18 (bugfix release and minor feature enhancement)
* Updated filesystem tools: e2fsprogs-1.42.9 and sys-block/partclone-0.2.69
* Updated GParted to 0.18.0 (Bug fix release)
* Updated app-backup/dar-2.4.12 (Disk-Archiver)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.0.0 (2014-01-15)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.10.25 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels: latest stable linux-3.12.7 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated XOrg graphical environment and drivers to xorg-server-1.14.3
* Updated GParted to 0.17.0 (Add support for online resize)
* Updated btrfs utilities to sys-fs/btrfs-progs-3.12

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.8.1 (2013-10-28)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.66 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.10.17 (altker32 + altker64)
* Update filesystem tools: e2fsprogs-1.42.8 + xfsprogs-3.1.11 + xfsdump-3.1.3
* Updated memtest86+ to verison 5.01 (available in floppy disk boot images)
* Updated XOrg graphical environment and drivers to xorg-server-1.13.4

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.8.0 (2013-09-18)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.62 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels: Long-Term-Supported linux-3.10.12 (altker32 + altker64)
* Added support for Gluster-3.4 filesystem (sys-cluster/glusterfs-3.4.0-r1)
* Updated btrfs utilities to sys-fs/btrfs-progs-0.20_rc1_p358
* Updated GParted to 0.16.2 (bug fix release)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.7.1 (2013-07-15)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.52 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.9.10 (altker32 + altker64)
* Enabled CONFIG_X86_X32 in recent kernels to be able to chroot to x32 systems

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.7.0 (2013-06-05)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.47 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.9.4 (altker32 + altker64)
* Downgraded gcc to 4.4 in order to produce smaller binaries and save space
* Fixed crash when booting from NBD (Many thanks to Gernot for the fix)
* Added sys-fs/safecopy for recovery from damaged (io-errors) devices or files

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.6.0 (2013-05-10)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.44 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.9.1 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated GParted to 0.16.1 (another critical bug fix release)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.5.1 (2013-04-28)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.42 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.8.9 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated GParted to 0.16.0 (critical bug fix release) and midori to 0.5.0

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.5.0 (2013-03-25)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.37 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.8.4 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated GParted to 0.15.0 and e2fsprogs to 1.42.7

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.4.2 (2013-03-05)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.35 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.7.10 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated fsarchiver to 0.6.17 (bugfix release and minor feature enhancement)
* Fixed support for booting via NBD which was in conflict with Network-Manager
* Added bootinfoscript which writes reports provinding info about the system

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.4.1 (2013-02-21)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.32 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.7.9 (altker32 + altker64)
* Removed support for "nonm" network boot option as NetworkManager is required
* Fixed network configuration options that can be passed to the boot command line

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.4.0 (2013-02-18)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.30 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.7.8 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated btrfs-progs filesystem utilities to latest snapshot (0.20_rc1_p56)
* Disabled power-saving options (CONFIG_SUSPEND and CONFIG_HIBERNATION)
* Added app-arch/star-1.5.2 (enhanced tar as well as enhanced mt/rmt)
* Updated fsarchiver to 0.6.16 (bugfix release), midori to 0.4.8

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.3.0 (2013-01-24)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.27 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.7.4 (altker32 + altker64)
* Fixed "waiting for uevents to be processed" by upgrading udev to 197-r4
* Updated XFS Filesystem utilities: xfsprogs-3.1.10 + xfsdump-3.1.2
* Updated app-backup/dar-2.4.9 (Disk-Archive 2.4.9)
* Added x11-misc/grsync-1.1.1 (A gtk frontend to rsync)
* Added sys-fs/fuse-exfat-1.0.0 (exFAT filesystem FUSE module)
* Fixed Network-Manager applet in the graphical environment
* Rebased genkernel on latest upstream version
* Updated sys-fs/ntfs3g to 2013.1.13

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.2.0 (2013-01-07)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.24 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.6.11 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated Xorg environment and drivers to x11-base/xorg-server-1.13.0-r1
* Updated LVM (Logical Volume Manager) to sys-fs/lvm2-2.02.95-r4
* Updated Gentoo packages: portage-2.1.11.31, openrc-0.11.8
* Added sys-fs/ecryptfs-utils (eCryptfs userspace utilities)
* Updated GParted to 0.14.1 (bug fixes release)
* Fixed /etc/init.d/pxebootsrv service

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.1.2 (2012-12-05)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.2.34 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.6.9 (altker32 + altker64)
* Added ModemManager-0.6.0.0 (Modem and mobile broadband management libraries)
* Updated sys-fs/btrfs-progs to 0.20_rc1 (btrfs filesystem utilities)
* Updated sys-block/partclone to 0.2.56 and syslinux/isolinux 4.06
* Fixed support for samba based autorun scripts (ar_source="smbfs://...")
* Added app-crypt/nwipe (Program to securely erase disks)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.1.1 (2012-11-06)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.2.33 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.6.6 (altker32 + altker64)
* Re-introduced support for Reiser4 filesystem in the alternative kernels
* Fixed "rootpass=MyPaSsWoRd" boot option by updating USE flags for shadow
* Fixed bugs in the installation scripts for USB sticks
* Updated NetworkManager to 0.9.6.4

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.1.0 (2012-10-29)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standard kernels is Long-Term-Supported linux-3.2.32 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Alternative kernels updated to latest stable 3.6.4 (altker32 + altker64)
* Updated btrfs-progs utilities to recent upstream version (git-20121017)
* Updated e2fsprogs to 1.42.5, GParted to 0.14.0, linux-firmware-20120924
* Updated tcpdump-4.3.0, coreutils-8.16, util-linux-2.21.2, dd-rescue-1.28
* Updated midori-0.4.7, xorg-server-1.12.4, clamav-0.97.6, spacefm-0.7.10
* Added zerofree-1.0.1 (Utility to zero out all free space on a filesystem)
* The "docache" boot option must also cached the boot and efi directories
* Fixed bugs in the installation scripts for USB sticks

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.0.0 (2012-09-03)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Added support for loading extra modules as SRM files (System Rescue Modules)
* Added support for UEFI booting from the CDRom on x86_64 using GRUB-2.00 (efi.img)
* Updated standard kernels to Long-Term-Supported linux-3.2.28 (rescue32 + rescue64)
* Updated alternative kernels to Long-Term-Supported linux-3.4.9 (altker32 + altker64)
* The rescuecd kernel image has been renamed rescue32 for better consistency
* Configured isolinux to automatically use the 64bit kernel if CPU is capable
* Automatically use 64bit version of fsarchiver/memtester if CPU is capable
* Reorganized and updated isolinux configuration and help messages
* Added net-misc/pssh-2.2.1 (parallel versions of the openssh tools)
* Added open-vm-tools (open-source tools for VMware guests)
* Updated e2fsprogs to 1.42.5, GParted to 0.13.1, partclone to 0.2.50

